meanings.definition: A muscle of the upper back that connects the scapula to the vertebrae.
meanings.sent1: The rhomboidei helps move your shoulder blades.
meanings.sent2: I felt sore in my rhomboidei after lifting weights.
meanings.sent3: The rhomboidei muscle decided to take a break during my workout.
meanings.sent4: Her rhomboidei were as strong as steel cables.
meanings.sent5: The physical therapist focused on strengthening my rhomboidei.

meanings.definition: A geometric shape with four sides, none of which are parallel.
meanings.sent1: The kite had a rhomboidei shape in the sky.
meanings.sent2: I drew a rhomboidei on my math homework.
meanings.sent3: The rhomboidei pattern on the floor looked like a tilted square.
meanings.sent4: Her eyes sparkled like rhomboidei gems in the sunlight.
meanings.sent5: The rhomboidei figure stood out among the rectangles and circles.
